      },
      "date": "2016-04-21 22:22:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI could stop passing in the op_offset but then I would need to unroll the lprocfs_counter_inc() call. This brings up a good question. Currently the counter is incremented even if calling the md_ops function returns an error. If we unroll should the lprocfs_counter_inc() be called only on success of the md_ops function call. The other option is not to unroll the lprocfs_counter_inc() call.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
